args: I feared the worst at one point,\nbut am glad we were able to defeat it.
Elly, did you hurt your arm?
Sadly, yes. I am not used to fighting in a\ndress, and lost my balance a few—AAAH!
No, I shall be quite all ri—AAAARGH!
Ugh. I seem to have sprained my ankle.\nPerhaps these high heels were\nill-advised...
Then climb on my back and I'll carry you.\n...Oh, wait. I forgot about your arm.
Er, Your Highness? What are you...?
Wh-what?! No! I am fine!\nPlease put me down!
But you can't walk on that ankle.
I shall think of something! Just please,\nput me down! I can't handle this!
Easy, Elly! If you keep struggling,\nyou're going to—
I am so very sorry. My heart simply could\nnot handle... Er, I mean, I did not wish\nto burden you overmuch.
You shouldn't worry about that.\nStill, I think we're both a bit tired,\nso how about we stop and rest?
Yes, I think that might be best.
*sigh* Wedding dresses are exhausting—\nand in more ways than one.
I've never heard you sigh this much, Elly.\nBut I suppose you DID just fight off fiends\nin a wedding dress.
While I admit it to be a beautiful dress,\nI believe armor suits me better.
I dunno. The dress is pretty great on you.
It's because you say things like that\nwithout thinking that I...
...When I first became a Paladyn,\nI swore my body and soul to the goddess.
I haven't given a thought to the idea\nof marriage since that day.
But wearing this dress made me think on\nwhat would happen if I DID get married.
Even though we were acting back there,\nI never expected to swear my undying love\nto anyone other than Ilia.
I'm sorry. I know it was uncomfortable,\nbut it was all I could think of at the time.
No, I enjoyyyyy... Er, I mean...
I've never had a conversation such as that\nbefore, and it was actually quite...exciting.\nNot in the least bit unpleasant.
Heh. I suppose it would have been a\nonce-in-a-lifetime experience to swear\nyour undying love to a fiend.
Heh. It would have, at that.
I doubt I will have cause to say anything\nlike that to anyone again—fiend or human.
I take great pride in being a Paladyn.

That would not change if I were to marry,
and yet in that case, there would be times
where I had to prioritize my family—
especially if children were involved.
That would mean prioritizing myself\nover both the goddess and the people\nI have sworn to serve.
That is something I can never do, which is\nwhy I said today will be the first and last\ntime I speak of love in such a way.
You know, one of the Paladyns who\nused to guard Zethia got married\na few years back.
I saw then just how hard it was to gain\nthe Church's approval for a wedding.
Of course, she was very busy after she\nwas married, which meant others had\nto fill in for her duties more and more.
Exactly as I would have predicted.
But she was also SO much happier.
She also got stronger,\nboth in body and mind.
I would have thought having less time\nto train would make her weaker.
She said it was because she had\nmore to protect than before.
She even started looking out for me even\nthough I wasn't technically her charge.
She put both me and my sister at ease.
I never would have thought of marriage as\nbeing a source of strength for a Paladyn.
Anyway, all of this is to say that if you\nWERE to get married, I don't think it\nmeans you're neglecting your duties.
Honestly, I'd just be glad you were happy.
I'm sure everyone else feels the same—\nincluding the Church AND the goddess.
Thank you for your kindness,\nYour Highness.
(He is right—I can be a Paladyn and still\ndo other things with my life.)
(It is up to ME to decide my future!)
